  <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Create a short “Designer–Coder Manifesto” using <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> through <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>, each followed by a paragraph. No CSS. Feel the hierarchy and the outline.</p>

  <h4>Instructions</h4>
  <ol class="prep-list">
    <li>Inside the starter, add exactly one <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> as the page title and a <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> under it explaining the manifesto’s purpose.</li>
    <li>Add one each of <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h3&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h4&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h5&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>—each immediately followed by a <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> explaining that point.</li>
    <li>Keep levels in sensible order (don’t skip from H2 to H5).</li>
    <li>Wrap everything in a semantic container (<code>&lt;article&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>).</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="designer-coder-discussion">
    <h4>Connect to the Lens</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Designer:</strong> How does heading order create visual flow even without CSS?</li>
      <li><strong>Coder:</strong> How will the browser/assistive tech outline this document?</li>
      <li><strong>Link:</strong> Structure drives meaning; meaning drives design choices.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h4>Success Criteria</h4>
  <ul class="test-goals">
    <li>✓ Exactly one <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> + a paragraph under it</li>
    <li>✓ One each of <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code> … <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> with a paragraph under each</li>
    <li>✓ Uses <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;section&gt;</code></li>
    <li>✓ No skipped/illogical levels</li>
